description:
&lt;p&gt;You can expect a warm welcome at Milton Keynes University Hospital, our staff are friendly and welcoming. We listen to each other and work together to embed our Trusts values and behaviours.  At MKUH we appreciate our staff and reward them with an outstanding benefits package including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free on-site parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free tea and coffee&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great flexible working opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted gym membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lease car scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous annual leave and pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On site nursery (chargeable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive staff health and well-being programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Milton Keynes University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust, in partnership with the University of Buckingham, is a University Teaching Hospital; we conduct research and teaching on site to improve the care of our patients. The hospital is undergoing significant investment, and we are proud to be rated good by the CQC. Visit our website to catch up on our latest news.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen within the Endoscopy Unit for a Decontamination Technician.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department is operational from 7am – 7pm over a 6 day shift system. Your typical hours will be one week of earlies and one week of lates and the successful applicant will need to be able to work flexible shifts covering these hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In line with Trust policy the department aims to become a 7 day service, it is likely that operational hours will be reviewed to reflect this.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department runs an on-call service and the technician would be required to participate fully in the out of hours on-call rota (contracted to one week in every four).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role involves efficiently providing the correct handling, cleaning, decontamination maintenance and security of flexible endoscopes and related equipment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;No previous experience is required for this role as on ongoing training programme is in operation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Decontamination Technicians are given the opportunity to gain experience in Sterile Services once fully trained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills, organisational and interpersonal skills, as liaison with other disciplines is an integral part of this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
